docs.abstract: The corporate version of Google Calendar is ultimately controlled by its administrator, but you may still have a say on who can see your day.
docs.snippet: The corporate version of Google Calendar is ultimately controlled by its administrator, but you may still have a say on who can see your day.
docs.lead_paragraph: Q. My office uses the business version of Gmail and Google Calendar. Can other people see my appointments on Google Calendar even if I haven’t sent a sharing invitation?

headline.main: Keeping Personal Appointments Private on Google Calendar

docs.abstract: Most web browsers now update themselves, but if you’re not sure what version number you’re actually running, take a peek under the hood.
docs.snippet: Most web browsers now update themselves, but if you’re not sure what version number you’re actually running, take a peek under the hood.
docs.lead_paragraph: Q. How do I see what version of Google Chrome is on my computer?

docs.abstract: Facebook tracks even nonusers as they surf the web, and House members grilled Mark Zuckerberg, Facebook’s chief executive, about the practice during his second day of hearings.
docs.snippet: Facebook tracks even nonusers as they surf the web, and House members grilled Mark Zuckerberg, Facebook’s chief executive, about the practice during his second day of hearings.
docs.lead_paragraph: Mark Zuckerberg, Facebook’s chief executive, went to Capitol Hill this week to explain to members of Congress how the detailed personal information of up to 87 million Facebook users ended up in the hands of a voter-profiling company called Cambridge Analytica.

headline.main: What You Don’t Know About How Facebook Uses Your Data
headline.print_headline: How the Social Media Giant Collects and Uses Your Data

docs.abstract: Last year, Mozilla released a revamped version of its browser that gives surfers plenty to customize up front.
docs.snippet: Last year, Mozilla released a revamped version of its browser that gives surfers plenty to customize up front.
docs.lead_paragraph: Q. After many years, I started using the Firefox browser again, and the start page for this new version is covered with links and icons. Can I change it?

docs.abstract: Tim Cook and Ginni Rometty have recently criticized Facebook. But don’t expect a long lineup of other tech industry leaders to speak out anytime soon.
docs.snippet: Tim Cook and Ginni Rometty have recently criticized Facebook. But don’t expect a long lineup of other tech industry leaders to speak out anytime soon.
docs.lead_paragraph: The recent tribulations of Facebook, which has lurched from crisis to crisis over the last year, most recently over the handling of users’ personal data, has pushed a few of the industry’s most prominent names to speak out against the company.

headline.main: As Facebook Struggles, Rivals’ Leaders Stay (Mostly) Mum
headline.print_headline: As Facebook Struggles, Rivals Stay (Mostly) Mum

docs.abstract: Hard drives don’t last forever, but utility programs and careful observation can help you decide when it’s time to replace a backup drive.
docs.snippet: Hard drives don’t last forever, but utility programs and careful observation can help you decide when it’s time to replace a backup drive.
docs.lead_paragraph: Q. I’ve been backing up my computer to two different external hard drives — one made by Seagate and the other by Western Digital. The backup drives are now six years old. I know hard drives fail after a while, so when should I replace these drives with new ones?

headline.main: Monitoring the Health of a Backup Drive

docs.abstract: Mr. Navarro is in line for a promotion, sources close to the White House say, a sign more aggressive trade measures such as tariffs may be in store.
docs.snippet: Mr. Navarro is in line for a promotion, sources close to the White House say, a sign more aggressive trade measures such as tariffs may be in store.
docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — President Trump could soon promote Peter Navarro, a trade policy adviser, to a more powerful position in the White House, elevating a longtime trade skeptic who has found himself sidelined by more pro-trade voices inside the White House.

headline.main: Peter Navarro, a Top Trade Skeptic, Is Ascendant
headline.print_headline: Noted Trade Skeptic in Line for Promotion

docs.abstract: It has been six months since Amazon took over Whole Foods for $13.4 billion. Here are a handful of notable changes Amazon has made to Whole Foods so far.
docs.snippet: It has been six months since Amazon took over Whole Foods for $13.4 billion. Here are a handful of notable changes Amazon has made to Whole Foods so far.
docs.lead_paragraph: Some signs are subtle, like the “Whole Foods + Amazon” one near the bananas. Others are more obvious, like the kiosk with Amazon devices for sale.

headline.main: Bit by Bit, Whole Foods Gets an Amazon Touch
headline.print_headline: Whole Foods Gets Primed With the Amazon Treatment

docs.abstract: Citing a need for ‘a safe and inclusive environment,’ the agency behind a recent New York Times ad campaign severed ties with Ted Royer after an investigation.
docs.snippet: Citing a need for ‘a safe and inclusive environment,’ the agency behind a recent New York Times ad campaign severed ties with Ted Royer after an investigation.
docs.lead_paragraph: Droga5, a prominent advertising agency, fired its chief creative officer, Ted Royer, on Thursday after having placed him on leave earlier this week, citing a commitment to “maintaining a safe and inclusive environment for all our employees.”

headline.main: The Advertising Firm Droga5 Fires Its Chief Creative Officer
headline.print_headline: Top Advertising Agency Fires Its Chief Creative Officer
